comment: OMG...   It's not "Justice League Society of America", it's just "Justice Society of America".  Superman's ORIGINAL saying did NOT include "the American way", it was just "For truth and justice".  They added "The American Way" in the late 40's because of all the Communist paranoia.  As an American and a heavy comics reader (can you tell?), I am SO glad that "the American way" is finally gone.  Take care, -Eric

comment: It's weird, I'm not American but I'm a huge Superman fan and it just doesn't feel right to me that they changed it like that. Superman believes in traditional American values/morals as he was raised by American farmers and is an American citizen himself. It doesn't mean he's a mouthpiece of the US government at all in fact he goes up against them multiple times in the comics.  He just believes in the American dream because he believes it can motivate people to transform themselves to be better people.
